rComments: Great professor. Structures is difficult to make exciting and interesting but if you have a genuine interest in learning, he will do everything he can to help you out.

The lecture notes are great. But you won't pass the course on those alone. The homework is long (get comfy with 2 am SunR nights), and oddly worded. The office hours (for both prof and TA) are must haves for truly understanding the material. This course is static deformable bodies,  you need it for the fun stuff. Exams are slightly above HW.

I appreciated the powerpoints, but they weren't always clear. Examples were very simple, homework got ridiculously long and complicated. The grader we had was also really tough. He was very helpful in office hours. Exams had problems that weren't clear on how much you needed to solved to get credit.
